[
    {
        "id": "e-safety",
        "name": "E Safety",
        "headerColour": "linear-gradient(90deg,rgb(208,0, 86),rgb(246, 61, 95))",
        "headerColour2": "linear-gradient(90deg, rgb(190, 40, 96), rgb(236, 31, 65))",
        "description": "Welcome to your Introduction to E-Safety!",
        "whatBannerText": "What exactly is E-safety?",
        "whatBannerDesc": "Find out what E-safety is and how it can help you browse the internet safely!",

        "what": [
            {
                "id": "intro-text",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-1.svg",
                "text": "When discussing internet safety, the threats posed can generally be broken down into 2 categories. These are information security and personal safety."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-electricity",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-2.svg",
                "text": "Information security is described as the personal information of a user that is kept online. This could be information such as their name, address, passwords and banking details."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-items",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-3.svg",
                "text": "This type of information is usually associated with users private details, resulting in issues for a user if these details are leaked."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-home-appliances",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-4.svg",
                "text": "Unauthorised access to these kinds of details could result in consequences such as identity theft, online theft and theft of property."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-automotive",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-5.svg",
                "text": "Scams that are commonly associated with accessing a user's private details include phishing scams and internet scams. "
            },
            {
                "id": "code-tv",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-1.svg",
                "text": "These scams occur when someone attempts to deceive a user, to make the user trust them enough to give away personal information."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-tweet",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-2.svg",
                "text": "Phishing scams often occur through email, but can occur anywhere on the internet. They involve scammers disguising themselves as a trustworthy source, in an attempt to gain access to the users personal details."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-console",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-3.svg",
                "text": "The websites used to deceive the user are often disguised to look very similar to the one they are mimicking, so that the user does not get suspicious of them."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-microwave",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-4.svg",
                "text": "Internet scams are slightly different and slightly less common than phishing but still extremely harmful. Internet scams aim to cheat a user out of their personal property through false promises and confidence tricks."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-lines",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-5.svg",
                "text": "This could occur when someone lies online in order to get something from another internet user. An example of this could be buying an item from a seller online, only to find out the seller lied to you about the price, quality, size, appearance, etc"
            },
            {
                "id": "code-rely",
                "image": "/images/e-safety/SVGs/what-1.svg",
                "text": "Another type of information security threat is Malware. Malware is a malicious software that is disguised as safe software  to acquire and use private information (such as passwords) without the users consent."
            } 
        ],
        "whyBannerText": "Why do we code?",
        "whyBannerDesc": "Find out why us humans are so fond of programming and coding!",
        "why": [
            {
                "id": "code-precice",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Code is a precise set of instructions explaining exactly what you want the computer to do at any given moment. "
            },
            {
                "id": "code-react",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Computers need to know exactly how to react to things, whether clicking a button or tapping the screen."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-direction",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "It’s like giving directions to someone on how to get somewhere."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-consider",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "You don’t only need to give the directions, you also have to give solutions for other elements that need to be considered."
            },
            {
                "id": "code-example",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "For example, what if there is a traffic jam? Or what if your car breaks down?"
            },
            {
                "id": "code-circumstance",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "You need to tell the computer what to do in these circumstances and how to behave."
            }

        ],
